job_description:
The Treasury and Financial Services Business Partner - FinCrime role is part of the broader Treasury team, dealing with all types of Treasury core activities such as payments management, banking, cash management, foreign exchange etc. but as well Financial Services Business Partnership.

FinCrime includes: anti-bribery and anti-corruption, sanctions and trade controls, anti-money laundering and anti-tax evasion. Role strives to support Treasury and Finance, and ultimately the Legal and Compliance team to enable the identification of compliance gaps and support Finance SMEs in the creation of SOX/ Business Control processes in the Financial Crime domain. This could be related to financial transaction/ funds flow analysis, books and records accounting controls, case management support and creation of framework/ playbook. This is done through proactive business partnering with the Legal and Compliance team and with close collaboration with the wider Finance (e.g. Risk & Control, O2C, Tax, Procurement, etc.) and other organizations.

The role will also actively participate in the FCRM oversight committee to support the overall enablement of compliance commitments and objectives set by the Committee. They will also help review and contribute to assessments initiated by the FCRM program office, participate in enabling collective recommendations to the Booking.com risk committee (as required) and join FinCrime crisis meetings as the need arises.

B.Responsible:

Min. 5 years of professional experience in Legal, Compliance, Treasury and/ or Finance in Financial Services industry
Lead Point of Contact (POC) and Business Partner for Treasury and Financial Crime topics;
Support Legal and Compliance team as required on FinCrime’s Treasury & Finance gaps analysis (inline with EU and OFAC regulations and other sanctions regimes, UK Bribery Act, EU AML directives and other global equivalents), financial transaction/ funds flow and case investigation;
Lead the creation of FinCrime Finance Playbook including guidelines on banking partners inquiries and due diligence. Further, framework management of such partners in high risk markets;
Support and work closely with Finance SMEs for the implementation of FinCrime SOX/ Business controls processes and as well as policies and procedures in wider Finance organization such as Treasury, Procurement, O2C, Accounting and Tax;
Actively participate in FCRM Oversight Committee activities and contribute in delivering its commitments and objectives. Help promote training/ awareness on Financial Crime topics as part of overall change management program.
Strategic Treasury and Finance FinCrime project lead. Coordinate and program manage various compliance requests related to financial flows (e.g. volumes in high risk countries, financial transactions investigation related to collection and payout, etc.);
Responsible for understanding, implementing and managing new product and/or commercial requirements related (but not limited) to Connected Trip initiatives (E.g. Flights, Insurance, etc.) Booking Holdings Financial Services (BHFS) and Regulated Products (E.g. FX Services, VCC self issuance, SME lending, etc.) from Treasury and Financial Services capacity;
Lead and own overall design of Treasury funds flow model that enables sound financial and operational risk management and safeguarding of funds
Actively promotes innovation and aspires to process improvements, best practices. Advocate for Treasury and Financial Services standards, framework guidance/ playbook and priorities;
Map out the value chain deliverables and financial economics of each solution;
Support in assessing financial Risks (FX, liquidity and counterparty) attached to new products and/or partners by working closely with risk owners, subject matter experts or parties within the first line of defense. Consider regulatory and operational implications;
Engage with external partners/ vendors such as FinTech and Banks as required, as well as internal / external counsels to support regulatory due diligence, fund flow design and implementation;
Assess whether existing Treasury and Financial Services products and/ or processes can be demonstrated to support the business or whether new solutions or operating models are required to accommodate new requirements;
Work closely with Program Management functions within Treasury & Financial Services and wider Finance to ensure streamlined organization of projects and resources;
Continuously liaise with key stakeholders across the business to understand priorities, requirements and to provide feedback on progress from a Treasury and Finance perspective;
Work closely with SMEs across the Treasury and wider Finance department to identify and implement best market practices and solutions;
Support to identify and enable incremental innovation based on strategic financial services and FinTech market development to support Product and/ or commercial teams;

B.Skilled:

Min. 5 years of professional experience in Legal, Compliance, Treasury and/ or Finance in Financial Services industry
Excellent English speaker with strong communication skills, able to adapt style and approach in order to work effectively with internal and external partners from a variety of different cultures;
Aligning with Booking.com’s Values (Think Customer First, Succeed Together, Own It, Learn Forever, Do the Right Thing); Being curious, flexible, and a creative & pragmatic problem solver
Master degree/ specialized advanced diploma in Financial Crime such as AML, regulatory, etc.is an advantage;
Able to keep the overview of several complex tasks / projects that run at the same time;
Strong passion for innovation and innovative technology such as RegTech, distributed ledger/ block chain, artificial intelligence and machine learning;
Experienced in project implementation and/ or change management;
Broad knowledge of micro and macroeconomic factors, with the ability to translate these into risk-based decisions;
Able to demonstrate relentless tenacity to drive business objectives and deliver results;
Excellent people & stakeholder management skills required


B.offered:

We are a performance-based company that offers career advancement and lucrative compensation, including bonus. We also offer what is called the “Booking Deal” with competitive benefits. This position is open to any candidate globally and in the case of relocation, we will assist you with a generous relocation package, ensuring a smooth transition to working and living in The Netherlands.
Pre-Employment Screening:

If your application is successful, your personal data may be used for a pre-employment screening check by a third party as permitted by applicable law. Depending on the vacancy and applicable law, a pre-employment screening may include employment history, education and other information (such as media information) that may be necessary for determining your qualifications and suitability for the position.

Booking.com continues to develop new products (i.e. adding other travel related products on our platform) and global Indirect tax regulations continue to change, especially for platforms. That’s why we are looking for additional expertise to grow our tax team. The main focus of this role is to help coordinate and manage a portfolio of complex global tax matters for Booking.com in the areas of VAT and/or local tax collection that may span across multiple departments, domains and/or geographies. You will also help manage the relationships with our tax advisors.

As Senior Tax Consultant - Indirect Tax you will work for Booking.com in Amsterdam (Booking.com’s headquarters), where our entire tax department sits. You will report directly to one of the (Senior) Tax Managers. The tax department currently consists of over 40 persons, responsible for various disciplines including CIT, DST, Transfer Pricing, VAT, Tax accounting. The tax department is part of Booking.com’s international Finance team (approx. 1000 professionals, mostly based in Amsterdam).

The role involves close interaction within our entire tax team, our parent company (Booking Holdings Group based in Norwalk, Connecticut), our international offices, business managers, functional teams and other finance colleagues. Therefore, it is essential that you have excellent management and communication skills in English.

Due to the rapid changes in the organization, the tasks and duties of this role may evolve over time. You should be keen to develop and grow within the role and to take on additional challenges and responsibilities as they occur.

You will be responsible for:

Work on key indirect tax challenges in different areas of content and geographies;
Help coordinate & manage (a portfolio of) complex indirect tax matters that may span across multiple departments, domains and/or geographies;
Proactively support (Senior) Tax Managers with their end to end responsibility from scoping the issue/challenge to the overall solution, including stakeholder management, driving issue resolution, initiating the needed change management and monitoring;
Liaise and collaborate with our Governance Controversy & Compliance team and Data & Technology Strategy team regarding global tax compliance across the business;
Help coordinate & manage the work of our tax advisors.

You will be skilled at:

University degree in Tax Economics/Law or similar degree;
Preferably between 3 to 5 years of working experience within an international environment;
Experience with digital economy/e-commerce would be a big plus;
Organized, proactive, energetic, critical mindset, results oriented, ability to be hands on deliverer;
Accurate, able to work under pressure and to strict deadlines, and comfortable working in a fast turnaround environment and managing multiple priorities simultaneously;
Analytical and being able to work with data would be a plus;
Excellent communication skills (both written and verbal) in English;
Pre-Employment Screening.
Pre-Employment Screening:

If your application is successful, your personal data may be used for a pre-employment screening check by a third party as permitted by applicable law. Depending on the vacancy and applicable law, a pre-employment screening may include employment history, education and other information (such as media information) that may be necessary for determining your qualifications and suitability for the position.

Are you a student of Fiscal Economics or Tax Law and are you interested in fields such as corporate income tax, dividend withholding tax, VAT and international tax? Are you ready to turn theory into practice? Are you interested in a seat on the ‘client’ side of the table instead of being the typical big4 consultant? And are you able to translate dusty tax lingo for non-tax people? Look no further! Join the tax team of the fastest growing digital agency in the world.

We are looking for a working student in team Tax during a period of three to six months. You will spend two or three days a week at DEPT®’s Rotterdam office and experience for yourself what it is like to work in an international company and to provide tax advice to various stakeholders as an inhouse tax advisor. You will work together with the rest of the Tax team on the day-to-day tasks and perform analyses that support decision making of your fellow Tax colleagues, our business and other supporting departments. You will of course be well supervised by experienced Tax colleagues who can teach you the tricks of the trade. During your working studentship you will be able to frequently collaborate with other colleagues, both nationally and internationally.

What are your responsibilities?

As a Tax working student at DEPT®, you

Work together with colleagues on tax questions relating to e.g. corporate income taxes, transfer pricing, VAT and tax treaties;
Liaise directly with tax advisors around the globe;
Execute analyses to support our Tax team;
Work with financial and business data;
Learn how to translate your findings into easy to understand content for non-tax people.

Do you recognize yourself in the following?

You are eager to learn;
You are an all-rounder in the field of tax who is not afraid of new challenges and who gets energy from varied tasks;
You are proactive and have a hands-on mentality;
You are flexible and communicative;
You are a team player and enjoy meeting new people;
You are in your third or fourth year of your university study Tax Law or Fiscal Economics;
You have experience with the Dutch Tax Law;
You are available a minimum 2 days per week, from May 2023 for a duration of 3-6 months;
You are fluent in Dutch and English.

Tax at DEPT®:

We strongly support diversity and are committed to create an inclusive environment for everyone at DEPT®. Ultimately, we are looking for a unique individual who wants to strengthen our work and community. In addition, we offer:

A small but ‘gezellig’ tax team that is responsible for all tax related matters on a global scale;
Working together with diverse teams with different levels of education & professional experience. Some colleagues have been here since the foundation of DEPT®, others joined no more than a month ago;
Tasks that contribute to your personal and professional development. If you grow, we grow. That’s why we’ll cheer you on (and support you) with personal coaching, a development plan and budget;
Good vibes: we trust and believe in creative freedom and autonomy;
Projects that work as well for you as the other way around. From short and snappy to more in-depth: whatever fits your ambition;
We strive to support the company’s stakeholders with meaningful advice and counseling;
Best of both worlds: the pros of an international leading agency with the energy & ambition of a global scaling company.
Fun informal activities, such as drinks at our bars in our offices.

About DEPT®:

DEPT® is a pioneering technology and marketing services company that creates integrated end-to-end digital experiences for brands such as Google, KFC, Philips, Audi, Twitch, Patagonia, eBay and more. Its team of 4,000+ digital specialists across 30+ locations on 5 continents delivers pioneering work on a global scale with a boutique culture. DEPT® is committed to making a positive impact on the planet and since 2021 has been Climate Neutral and B Corporation certified. Learn more about our diversity, equity, and inclusion efforts here or visit our <<careers page>> to find out more about culture and growth opportunities at DEPT®. Benefits at DEPT®:

DEPT® has been named A Great Place To Work in 2022 and certified B-Corp® since 2021 – award winning in the best way possible.
Awesome clients. Whether big, small, local or global — at DEPT® you’ll get the opportunity to work with all of them. And we celebrate all of our successes together!
Opportunities to develop your skills even further through training and certifications.
Everything to focus on your health: from free bootcamp to yoga lessons, mindfulness sessions, mental health services, serious discounts on sport memberships, healthy lunches at the office, and above all: a safe work environment.
Great fringe benefits; use of OV-bikes, an NS Business Card and many other goodies.
You can discover even more employee benefits here.

Interested?

Are you excited? Please submit your motivation letter and CV in Dutch or English.

Even if you don’t meet all the requirements or have a different work background, consider applying for this vacancy if you think you are the right fit for the job! Of course we love talent, but we’re also looking for a suitable addition to our DEPT® culture. Because that’s what makes everything more fun: from Monday morning meetings to Friday afternoon mixers and everything in between.

Please note: to be eligible for this internship, you are required to be living and studying in the Netherlands.
